National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: Moultonboro, NH
Accident Number: ERA11CA303
Date & Time: 05/01/2011, 1600 EDT
Registration: N61980
Aircraft: CHAMPION 7EC-703
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Loss of control on ground
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis The pilot reported that, during the landing rollout, a strong wind gust caused him to lose directional control of the airplane.
The airplane veered off of the runway and collided with trees.
During the accident sequence, the airplane incurred substantial damage to the wing spars.
A witness at the airport confirmed the weather anomaly at the time of the accident.
The nearest airport's weather observation system reported at the time of the accident that the wind was light and variable.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: The pilotâ„¢s loss of directional control during the landing rollout, which resulted in a collision with trees.
